Introduction¶

Data: The analysis is performed on the soccer database which comes from Kaggle. It contains data for soccer matches, players, and teams from several European countries from 2008 to 2016.

Questions:

  • 1. Which teams improved the most over the time period?
  • 2. What team attributes lead to the most home team victories?
  • 3. Which player had the most penalties?

Code for retrieving teams data into a csv file from SQLite database: ``` WITH t1 as (SELECT c.name country_name,l.name league_name, m.id match_id, m.season, m.stage, m.date, m.home_team_goal, m.away_team_goal, t.team_long_name home_team, t.team_short_name home_team_abbr, ta.chanceCreationPassing, ta.chanceCreationPassingClass, ta.chanceCreationShooting, ta.chanceCreationShootingClass, ta.defencePressure, ta.defencePressureClass

FROM Country as c JOIN League as l on c.id = l.country_id JOIN Match as m on l.id = m.league_id JOIN Team as t on m.home_team_api_id = t.team_api_id JOIN Team_Attributes as ta on t.team_api_id = ta.team_api_id order by m.date DESC),

t2 as (SELECT m.id match_id, t.team_long_name away_team, t.team_short_name away_team_abbr FROM Match as m JOIN Team as t on m.away_team_api_id = t.team_api_id)

SELECT t1.*, t2.away_team, t2.away_team_abbr FROM t1 JOIN t2 on t1.match_id = t2.match_id ```

def check_value3(cell_value = 0):
    if cell_value > 0:
        return 'w'
    elif cell_value == 0:
        return 'd'
    else:
        return 'l'

Analyzing home and away statistics of teams¶

In [151]:

The distribution is also positively skewed depicting majority of the away teams scoring utmost 1 goal.

In [152]:

It shows that majority of the teams have won their home matches with 3 points having the highest frequency.

In [153]:
# Plotting the distribution of away points
df['away_points'].hist();

It shows that majority of the teams have lost their away matches with 0 point having the highest frequency.

In [154]:
# Plotting the distribution of home win
df['home_win'].hist();
In [155]:
# Plotting the distribution of away win
df['away_win'].hist();

As expected from the home points and away points distribution, the above home and away win plots depicting insignificant difference between the win and lose/draw for home matches which becomes significant when it comes to away matches. Hence, it is evident that winning away matches is difficult as compared to home matches and teams with high away win records are expected to be higher in the overall ranking of top teams over the period.

Conclusions¶

Celtic, Manchester United, FC Bayern Munich, Real Madrid CF and Juventus have been the most successful teams over the time period 2008-2016 with Celtic gaining the most points, followed by Manchester United, FC Bayern Munich, Real Madrid CF and Juventus respectively.

Moreover, exploratory data analysis revealed that home team goal, home points have positive relationship with home wins whereas away team goal and away points have negative relationship with home wins.

Romain Bregerie, a right-footed player with a medium attacking and defensive work rate, having an overall FIFA rating of 68 (out of 100) had the most i.e. 44 penalties in the time period 2008-2016.

Limitations¶

Teams having played eleven less matches at home as compared to away and thus influencing the result of most successful teams as the result is dependent on both home and away win records and favouring teams with high away win records.

Further investigation is required by taking into account the goal difference and other build-up play, defense (aggression, teamwidth) attributes which were not included in the selected data for analysis in order to determine the overall attributes leading to most home wins.

The finishing and shot power of Roman Bregerie during the time period was very low i.e. 15 and 11 respectively, leading to further investigate the result of him being the best penalty taker with most penalties under his name.
